{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01SyFUknSm9GrjnHKBYQ69oX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to build a wrapper class for reading from an SSH bytestream. Let me understand the requirements:\n\n1. Constructor takes a stream\n2. Method to read a fixed number of bytes from it\n3. If fewer bytes than requested remain in the stream, raise an EOFError\n\nThis is a straightforward task. I need to create a class that:\n- Stores the stream in the constructor\n- Has a method (typically called `read`) that takes a number of bytes\n- Reads that many bytes from the stream\n- Raises EOFError if there aren't enough bytes\n\nHere's what I'll implement:\n\n```python\nclass SSHByteStreamReader:\n    def __init__(self, stream):\n        self.stream = stream\n    \n    def read(self, num_bytes):\n        data = self.stream.read(num_bytes)\n        if len(data) < num_bytes:\n            raise EOFError(f\"Expected {num_bytes} bytes but only got {len(data)}\")\n        return data\n```\n\nThis is a simple wrapper that:\n1. Takes a stream in the constructor\n2. Has a `read` method that takes the number of bytes to read\n3. Reads from the stream\n4. Checks if we got fewer bytes than requested, and raises EOFError if so\n\nLet me write this to candidate.py.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4674,"cache_read_input_tokens":24095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4674},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01f3b59d-4fa7-475d-a3a2-f7352f6a0375","uuid":"b32e137d-d49b-4233-9653-cd398155eb92","request_id":"req_011CbdNHq7yk8f1cT7gJhzQJ"}
